usdERXSysMIB.name: usdERXSysMIB

revisions.description: Added new line card types: X.21/V.35, Ut3f12, Ue3f12, Cocx-F3.

Modified the following objects: usdERXSysTempFanStatus usdERXSysTempStatus Added the following objects: usdERXSysTempProtectionStatus usdERXSysTempProtectionHoldOffTime usdERXSysTempProtectionHoldOffTimeRemaining Added the following notification: usdERXSysTempProtectionStatusChange

Added the following objects: usdERXSysMemUtilPct usdERXSysMemCapacity usdERXSysHighMemUtilThreshold usdERXSysAbatedMemUtilThreshold usdERXSysMemUtilTrapEnable Added the following notifications: usdERXSysHighMemUtil usdERXSysAbatedMemUtil
Added support for system timing parameters. Added usdERXSysSlotDescr to usdERXSysSlotOperStatusChange trap.
Added board serial number, assembly number and assembly revision.
Added OC-12 card and Dual FE card support. Added redundancy/reversion and boot record configuration support.
Initial version of this MIB module.

usdERXSysMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdERXSysMIB.description: MIB objects for managing ERX Edge Router systems.

UsdTimingSelector.name: UsdTimingSelector
UsdTimingSelector.description: The system timing selector. A value of 1 corresponds to the primary timing selector. A value of 2 corresponds to the secondary timing selector. A value of 3 corresponds to the tertiary timing selector. A value of 4 indicates an error with the timing selector.

UsdTimingSourceType.name: UsdTimingSourceType
UsdTimingSourceType.description: The set of selectable timing source types. The timing source type determines the timing source parameters.

UsdTimingSourceLineType.name: UsdTimingSourceLineType
UsdTimingSourceLineType.description: The set of choices for line type timing.

UsdSysCardType.name: UsdSysCardType
UsdSysCardType.description: The type of card in a system slot: unknown Unknown type. srp Switch/Route Processor. ct3 Channelized T3. oc3 OC-3 (SONET/SDH). ut3Atm Unchannelized T3 (ATM service). ut3Frame Unchannelized T3 (Frame service). ue3Atm Unchannelized E3 (ATM service). ue3Frame Uncahnnelized E3 (Frame service). ce1 Channelized E1. ct1 Channelized T1. dpfe Dual Port Fast Ethernet. oc12Pos OC-12 (POS/SDH). oc12Atm OC-12 (ATM service). oc3Pos Quad OC-3 (POS/SDH). oc3Atm Quad OC-3 (ATM service). ge Gigabit Ethernet. fe8 Fast Ethernet 8-port. oc3oc12Pos Generic OC3/OC12 POS (multi-personality). oc3oc12Atm Generic OC3/OC12 ATM (multi-personality). coc3oc12 Channelized generic OC3/OC12 (multi-personality). coc3 Channelized OC3. coc12 Channelized OC12. oc12Server OC-12 Rate Server Card. hssi High Speed Serial Interface. geFe Generic GE/FE (multi-personality). ct3P12 Channelized T3 12-port. v35 X.21/V.35 Card. ut3f12 Unchannelized T3 12-port. ue3f12 Unchannelized E3 12-port. coc3F3 OC-3 channelized to T3. coc12F3 OC-12 channelized to T3. cocxF3 12-port T3/E3 or OC3/OC12 (multi-personality).

usdERXSysChassisRev.name: usdERXSysChassisRev
usdERXSysChassisRev.description: Chassis revision number. If unknown, the value 255 is reported.

usdERXSysSwBuildDate.name: usdERXSysSwBuildDate
usdERXSysSwBuildDate.description: Build date of currently executing operational software version.

usdERXSysRevertControl.name: usdERXSysRevertControl
usdERXSysRevertControl.description: Global revert control: off Disable global revert. immediate All slots are to revert immediately (asap). timeOfDay All slots are to revert at time specified by usdRxSysRevertTimeOfDay. This object/value must be set concurrently with usdERXSysRevertTimeOfDay.

usdERXSysRevertTimeOfDay.name: usdERXSysRevertTimeOfDay
usdERXSysRevertTimeOfDay.description: The number of seconds past midnight on any given day at which time reverts are allowed to occur. This object must be set concurrently with usdERXSysRevertControl.

usdERXSysBootConfigControl.name: usdERXSysBootConfigControl
usdERXSysBootConfigControl.description: System boot configuration control: file Revert to configuration settings specified by usdERXSysBootConfigFile. The usdERXSysBootConfigControl and usdERXSysBootConfigFile must be specified together in the same set request PDU. fileOnce Revert to configuration settings specified by usdERXSysBootConfigFile. Do not continue to use file after using it once. The usdERXSysBootConfigControl and usdERXSysBootConfigFile must be specified together in the same set request PDU. factoryDefaults Revert to factory default settings. runningConfiguration Revert to current settings.

usdERXSysBootBackupConfigControl.name: usdERXSysBootBackupConfigControl
usdERXSysBootBackupConfigControl.description: System boot backup configuration control: file Revert to backup configuration settings specified by usdERXSysBootBackupConfigFile. The usdERXSysBootBackupConfigControl and usdERXSysBootBackupConfigFile must be specified together in the same set request PDU. factoryDefaults Revert to factory default settings. none Specify no backup.

usdERXSysBootForceBackupControl.name: usdERXSysBootForceBackupControl
usdERXSysBootForceBackupControl.description: System boot force backup control: off Do not force revert to backup settings. on Do force revert to backup settings.

usdERXSysBootAutoRevertControl.name: usdERXSysBootAutoRevertControl
usdERXSysBootAutoRevertControl.description: System boot auto revert control: default Use default auto-revert tolerances. never Never auto-revert to backup. set Set auto-revert settings at specified tolerances.

usdERXSysBootAutoRevertCountTolerance.name: usdERXSysBootAutoRevertCountTolerance
usdERXSysBootAutoRevertCountTolerance.description: The auto-revert reboot count tolerance. This object cannot be set to zero, but may contain a zero value when the control is set to never(1).

usdERXSysBootAutoRevertTimeTolerance.name: usdERXSysBootAutoRevertTimeTolerance
usdERXSysBootAutoRevertTimeTolerance.description: The auto-revert reboot time tolerance. This object cannot be set to zero, but will contain a zero value when the control is set to never(1).

usdERXSysBootReleaseFile.name: usdERXSysBootReleaseFile
usdERXSysBootReleaseFile.description: The local boot release file name, with extension .rel.

usdERXSysBootConfigFile.name: usdERXSysBootConfigFile
usdERXSysBootConfigFile.description: The local boot configuration file name, with extension .cnf. The usdERXSysBootConfigControl and usdERXSysBootConfigFile must be specified together in the same set request PDU.

usdERXSysBootBackupReleaseFile.name: usdERXSysBootBackupReleaseFile
usdERXSysBootBackupReleaseFile.description: The local backup boot release file name, with extension .rel.

usdERXSysBootBackupConfigFile.name: usdERXSysBootBackupConfigFile
usdERXSysBootBackupConfigFile.description: The local backup boot configuration file name, with extension .cnf. The usdERXSysBootBackupConfigControl and usdERXSysBootBackupConfigFile must be specified together in the same set request PDU.

usdERXSysAdminTimingSource.name: usdERXSysAdminTimingSource
usdERXSysAdminTimingSource.description: The administrative timing source for the ERX system. The ERX periodically monitors the status of three timing sources, primary, secondary and tertiary. If the systems current timing source fails, the system will automatically downgrade to the next timing source. If the system is configured to automatically upgrade (usdERXSysTimingDisableAutoUpgrade is set to false(2)) the system will switch back to the higher timing source when it becomes available. A timing source failure can be detected by comparing the operational and admin timing sources. If they are not equal, the system has swapped timing sources because the administratively set value is in the error state.

usdERXSysOperTimingSource.name: usdERXSysOperTimingSource
usdERXSysOperTimingSource.description: The operations timing source for the ERX system. The ERX periodically monitors the status of three timing sources, primary, secondary and tertiary. If the systems current timing source fails, the system will automatically downgrade to the next timing source. If the system is configured to automatically upgrade (usdERXSysTimingDisableAutoUpgrade is set to false(2)) the system will switch back to the higher timing source when it becomes available.

usdERXSysTimingDisableAutoUpgrade.name: usdERXSysTimingDisableAutoUpgrade
usdERXSysTimingDisableAutoUpgrade.description: This object controls the automatic timing selector upgrade. Setting this object to true(1) will prevent automatic upgrade to the next highest timing selector. Setting this object to false(2) will enable the automatic upgrade of timing selectors.

usdERXSysTimingSelectorEntry.name: usdERXSysTimingSelectorEntry
usdERXSysTimingSelectorEntry.description: A table entry describing a system timing selector.

usdERXSysTimingSelectorIndex.name: usdERXSysTimingSelectorIndex
usdERXSysTimingSelectorIndex.description: The system timing selector index associated with this entry.

usdERXSysTimingSourceType.name: usdERXSysTimingSourceType
usdERXSysTimingSourceType.description: The system timing source type for this entry. This object must be present when setting either the usdERXSysTimingSourceIfIndex or usdERXSysTimingSourceLine objects. Also, if the value of this object is set to timingInternal(2), no other objects should be simultanously set, otherwise the agent will return an error.

usdERXSysTimingSourceIfIndex.name: usdERXSysTimingSourceIfIndex
usdERXSysTimingSourceIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface selected as the system timing source. The usdERXSysTimingSourceType object must be set to timingInterfaceIfIndex(1) otherwise setting this object will fail.

usdERXSysTimingSourceLine.name: usdERXSysTimingSourceLine
usdERXSysTimingSourceLine.description: The line type timing source for this entry. The usdRxSysTimingSourceType object must be set to timingLine(3) for the agent to accept a set to this object.

usdERXSysTimingStatus.name: usdERXSysTimingStatus
usdERXSysTimingStatus.description: The status associated with this system timing selector.

usdERXSysMemUtilPct.name: usdERXSysMemUtilPct
usdERXSysMemUtilPct.description: Percentage of system memory utilization. A value of -1 indicates the utilization is unknown.

usdERXSysMemCapacity.name: usdERXSysMemCapacity
usdERXSysMemCapacity.description: The total memory capacity of the system.

usdERXSysHighMemUtilThreshold.name: usdERXSysHighMemUtilThreshold
usdERXSysHighMemUtilThreshold.description: The value of system memory utilization, where if reached for the first time will generate a high memory utilization event to the management entity on this system. The value of this object must be greated than the value of usdERXSysAbatedMemUtilThreshold.

usdERXSysAbatedMemUtilThreshold.name: usdERXSysAbatedMemUtilThreshold
usdERXSysAbatedMemUtilThreshold.description: The value of system memory utilization that is used to determine when to generate an abated memory utilization event notification to the management entity on this system. The value of this object must be less than the value of usdERXSysHighMemUtilThreshold. The abated memory utilization trap is sent once if the high memory threshold was reached, and memory utilization falls to the value of this object.

usdERXSysMemUtilTrapEnable.name: usdERXSysMemUtilTrapEnable
usdERXSysMemUtilTrapEnable.description: Controls the sending of system memory utilization events. Setting the value of this object to true(1) will cause system memory utilization event notification, if they occur, to be sent to the management entity on this system. Setting the value of this object to false(2) will disable event notifications.

usdERXSysFabricSpeed.name: usdERXSysFabricSpeed
usdERXSysFabricSpeed.description: Speed of switching fabric, in gigabits per second.

usdERXSysFabricRev.name: usdERXSysFabricRev
usdERXSysFabricRev.description: Fabric revision number. If unknown, the value 255 is reported.

usdERXSysNvsStatus.name: usdERXSysNvsStatus
usdERXSysNvsStatus.description: Status of non-volatile storage (NVS): notPresent NVS is not installed. writeProtected NVS is write-protected. volumeError Status poll of NVS failed. nearCapacity Utilization exceeds 85% of NVS capacity. ok NVS is operational, none of the preceding conditions apply. nearConfigCapacity Utilization exceeds the ability to save the running configuration.

usdERXSysNvsCapacity.name: usdERXSysNvsCapacity
usdERXSysNvsCapacity.description: Capacity of NVS storage in megabytes.

usdERXSysNvsUtilPct.name: usdERXSysNvsUtilPct
usdERXSysNvsUtilPct.description: Percentage of NVS storage used. A value of -1 indicates NVS utilization is unknown.

usdERXSysSlotCount.name: usdERXSysSlotCount
usdERXSysSlotCount.description: The number of slots in the system.

usdERXSysSlotEntry.name: usdERXSysSlotEntry
usdERXSysSlotEntry.description: A table entry describing contents of a system slot.

usdERXSysSlotIndex.name: usdERXSysSlotIndex
usdERXSysSlotIndex.description: Slot number. NOTE: Slot numbers are zero-based.

usdERXSysSlotCurrentCardType.name: usdERXSysSlotCurrentCardType
usdERXSysSlotCurrentCardType.description: Type of card actually in the slot. This could be different from the type reported in usdERXSysSlotExpectedCardType, in which case it may be necessary to set usdERXSysSlotControl to 'flush' before this card can be made operational.

usdERXSysSlotRev.name: usdERXSysSlotRev
usdERXSysSlotRev.description: Revision number of the card. If unknown, the value 255 is reported.

usdERXSysSlotAdminStatus.name: usdERXSysSlotAdminStatus
usdERXSysSlotAdminStatus.description: Exerts administrative control to enable/disable the slot.

usdERXSysSlotDisableReason.name: usdERXSysSlotDisableReason
usdERXSysSlotDisableReason.description: Indicates the condition causing the slot to be disabled: none Value when card is not disabled. unknown Unknown reason for disablement. assessing The slot content is being assessed (transient initialization state). admin The slot is administratively disabled. cardMismatch The current card type conflicts with configuration associated with a different card type that previously occupied the slot. fabricLimit Card resource requirements exceed available fabric capacity. imageError Software image for card is missing or invalid.

usdERXSysSlotExpectedCardType.name: usdERXSysSlotExpectedCardType
usdERXSysSlotExpectedCardType.description: Type of card associated with this slot through prior presence. After the card is removed, this association persists (and inhibits operation of a different card type in this slot, if one is inserted) until usdERXSysSlotControl is set to 'flush'.

usdERXSysSlotControl.name: usdERXSysSlotControl
usdERXSysSlotControl.description: Administrative control of this slot: noOperation Setting this value has no effect. flush Flushes configuration associated with a card type that previously occupied this slot. Used to explicitly confirm that the slot is now empty, or contains a different card type. Card must be disabled when this value is asserted. See description for usdERXSysSlotDisableReason. reset Resets the slot. forceFailover Forces the slot to failover to backup. noBoot Deconfigure primary release file for the slot. noBootBackup Deconfigure backup release file for the slot.

usdERXSysSlotCpuUtilPct.name: usdERXSysSlotCpuUtilPct
usdERXSysSlotCpuUtilPct.description: Percentage of CPU utilization. A value of -1 indicates the utilization is unknown.

usdERXSysSlotMemUtilPct.name: usdERXSysSlotMemUtilPct
usdERXSysSlotMemUtilPct.description: Percentage of memory utilization. A value of -1 indicates the utilization is unknown.

usdERXSysSlotIoaPresent.name: usdERXSysSlotIoaPresent
usdERXSysSlotIoaPresent.description: Indicates whether the card's corresponding I/O adapter is present.

usdERXSysSlotPortCount.name: usdERXSysSlotPortCount
usdERXSysSlotPortCount.description: Number of physical ports for the EXPECTED card type for this slot. NOTE: In event of a card mismatch in this slot, the port count for the CURRENT card in this slot is not recognized/reported until the configuration for the EXPECTED card is explicitly flushed via usdERXSysSlotControl.

usdERXSysSlotLastChange.name: usdERXSysSlotLastChange
usdERXSysSlotLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime when the value of usdERXSysSlotOperStatus last changed.

usdERXSysSlotRedundancyLockout.name: usdERXSysSlotRedundancyLockout
usdERXSysSlotRedundancyLockout.description: Exerts administrative control to enable/disable Redundancy protection for the slot.

usdERXSysSlotRedundancyGroupId.name: usdERXSysSlotRedundancyGroupId
usdERXSysSlotRedundancyGroupId.description: Identifies the Redundancy group as derived from hardware settings.

usdERXSysSlotSpareServer.name: usdERXSysSlotSpareServer
usdERXSysSlotSpareServer.description: True only if the line card in slot is a spare redundant server.

usdERXSysSlotAssociatedSlot.name: usdERXSysSlotAssociatedSlot
usdERXSysSlotAssociatedSlot.description: If the module is a primary card and the spare is acting on its behalf, then the value of this object is the slot number of the associated spare. If the module is a primary card and is active (not spared), then the value of this object is the cards actual slot number. If the module is a spare card and it is active, then the value of this object is the slot number of the primary card that is being spared for. If the module is a spare and it is inactive, then the value of this object is the its own slot number. If module is not part of a redundancy group, or the slot is empty, the value of this object is 255.

usdERXSysSlotRevertControl.name: usdERXSysSlotRevertControl
usdERXSysSlotRevertControl.description: Per-slot revert control: off Disable slot revert. immediate Slot is to revert immediately (asap). timeAndDate Slot is to revert at time specified by usdRxSysSlotRedundancyRevertTime.

usdERXSysSlotRedundancyRevertTime.name: usdERXSysSlotRedundancyRevertTime
usdERXSysSlotRedundancyRevertTime.description: The date and time associated with the timeAndDate (delayed) revert operation.

usdERXSysSlotBootReleaseFile.name: usdERXSysSlotBootReleaseFile
usdERXSysSlotBootReleaseFile.description: The local boot release file name for this slot, with extension .rel.

usdERXSysSlotBootBackupReleaseFile.name: usdERXSysSlotBootBackupReleaseFile
usdERXSysSlotBootBackupReleaseFile.description: The local backup boot release file name for this slot, with extension .rel.

usdERXSysSlotSerialNumber.name: usdERXSysSlotSerialNumber
usdERXSysSlotSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the card in this slot.

usdERXSysSlotAssemblyPartNumber.name: usdERXSysSlotAssemblyPartNumber
usdERXSysSlotAssemblyPartNumber.description: The part number of the card in this slot.

usdERXSysSlotAssemblyRev.name: usdERXSysSlotAssemblyRev
usdERXSysSlotAssemblyRev.description: The revision number of the card assembly in this slot.

usdERXSysSlotIoaSerialNumber.name: usdERXSysSlotIoaSerialNumber
usdERXSysSlotIoaSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the I/O adaptor on the card in this slot.

usdERXSysSlotIoaAssemblyPartNumber.name: usdERXSysSlotIoaAssemblyPartNumber
usdERXSysSlotIoaAssemblyPartNumber.description: The part number of the I/O adaptor on the card in this slot.

usdERXSysSlotIoaAssemblyRev.name: usdERXSysSlotIoaAssemblyRev
usdERXSysSlotIoaAssemblyRev.description: The revision number of the I/O adaptor assembly on the card in this slot.

usdERXSysPortTable.name: usdERXSysPortTable
usdERXSysPortTable.description: Table of system physical ports. The information in this table reflects the ports for the EXPECTED card type in each slot; in event of a card mismatch, this table permits navigation of the existing configuration of the expected card type.

usdERXSysPortEntry.name: usdERXSysPortEntry
usdERXSysPortEntry.description: A table entry describing a physical port of the system.

usdERXSysPortIndex.name: usdERXSysPortIndex
usdERXSysPortIndex.description: Port number of this physical port, relative to the slot in which it resides. Each physical port is uniquely distinguished by its slot/port pair. NOTE: Port numbers are zero-based.

usdERXSysPortType.name: usdERXSysPortType
usdERXSysPortType.description: Type of the physical port: unknown Unknown port type. eth Ethernet. ct3 Channelized T3. oc3c OC-3c (SONET/SDH). ut3Atm Unchannelized T3 (ATM service). ut3Frame Unchannelized T3 (Frame service). ue3Atm Unchannelized E3 (ATM service). ue3Frame Unchannelized E3 (Frame service). ce1 Channelized E1. ct1 Channelized T1. oc12Pos OC-12 (POS/SDH). oc12Atm OC-12 (ATM service). oc3Pos OC-3 (POS/SDH). oc3Atm OC-3 (ATM service). coc3 Channelized OC-3. coc12 Channelized OC-12. oc12Server OC-12 (Server card). hssi High Speed Serial Interface. v35 X.21/V.35.

usdERXSysPortIfIndex.name: usdERXSysPortIfIndex
usdERXSysPortIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the Interfaces MIB ifTable entry corresponding to this physical port; if zero, the ifIndex is unknown or does not exist.

usdERXSysPowerEntry.name: usdERXSysPowerEntry
usdERXSysPowerEntry.description: A table entry describing status of a system power element.

usdERXSysPowerIndex.name: usdERXSysPowerIndex
usdERXSysPowerIndex.description: Arbitrary integer index to distinguish entries in this table.

usdERXSysPowerDescr.name: usdERXSysPowerDescr
usdERXSysPowerDescr.description: Textual description of this power element.

usdERXSysPowerStatus.name: usdERXSysPowerStatus
usdERXSysPowerStatus.description: The status of the power element: inactive No power available from this element. active Power available from this element.

usdERXSysTempFanStatus.name: usdERXSysTempFanStatus
usdERXSysTempFanStatus.description: Status of fan subsystem. ok All components operational warning The fan subsystem has a non-critical failure. failed The fan subsystem has a critical failure, or has been removed, and is now non-operational.

usdERXSysTempTable.name: usdERXSysTempTable
usdERXSysTempTable.description: Table of system temperature sensors. Sensors are distributed across the chassis, at least one sensor per populated slot.

usdERXSysTempEntry.name: usdERXSysTempEntry
usdERXSysTempEntry.description: A table entry describing status of a temperature sensor.

usdERXSysTempIndex.name: usdERXSysTempIndex
usdERXSysTempIndex.description: Arbitrary integer index to distinguish sensors associated with the same chassis slot.

usdERXSysTempStatus.name: usdERXSysTempStatus
usdERXSysTempStatus.description: The status of a temperature sensor: unknown unknown failed failed tooLow below nominal range nominal within nominal range tooHigh above nominal range tooLowWarning near lower limit tooHighWarning near upper limit

usdERXSysTempValue.name: usdERXSysTempValue
usdERXSysTempValue.description: The temperature measured by this sensor in degrees Celsius. This measurement is valid only if the value of the corresponding usdERXSysTempStatus is nominal.

usdERXSysTempProtectionStatus.name: usdERXSysTempProtectionStatus
usdERXSysTempProtectionStatus.description: Thermal protection status: monitoring monitoring inHoldOff hold off time has begun activatedHoldOffExpired hold off time has expired, the system is in thermal protection mode activatedTempTooHigh temperature too high, the system is in thermal protection mode

usdERXSysTempProtectionHoldOffTime.name: usdERXSysTempProtectionHoldOffTime
usdERXSysTempProtectionHoldOffTime.description: The time, in seconds, before the system enters thermal protection mode after a critical fan subsystem failure is detected.

usdERXSysTempProtectionHoldOffTimeRemain.name: usdERXSysTempProtectionHoldOffTimeRemaining
usdERXSysTempProtectionHoldOffTimeRemain.description: The time remaining, in seconds, before the system enters thermal protection mode while the thermal protection status is set to inHoldOff. The value decrements every second until it reaches zero, and the status changes to activatedHoldOffExpired. When the thermal protection status is not inHoldOff or activatedHoldOffExpired, the value is set to the hold off time.

usdERXSysSubsystemEntry.name: usdERXSysSubsystemEntry
usdERXSysSubsystemEntry.description: A table entry containing information pertaining to a subsystem.

usdERXSysSubsystemControl.name: usdERXSysSubsystemControl
usdERXSysSubsystemControl.description: Administrative control of this subsystem: noOperation Setting this value has no effect. noBoot Deconfigure primary release file for the subsystem. noBootBackup Deconfigure backup release file for the subsystem.

usdERXSysSubsystemBootReleaseFile.name: usdERXSysSubsystemBootReleaseFile
usdERXSysSubsystemBootReleaseFile.description: The local boot release file name for this subsystem, with extension .rel.

usdERXSysSubsystemBootBackupReleaseFile.name: usdERXSysSubsystemBootBackupReleaseFile
usdERXSysSubsystemBootBackupReleaseFile.description: The local backup boot release file name for this subsystem, with extension .rel.

usdERXSysSlotOperStatusChange.name: usdERXSysSlotOperStatusChange
usdERXSysSlotOperStatusChange.description: Reports a status change for a slot. This trap is generated on a transition into a stable state (online or disabled) or on a transition out of online.

usdERXSysPowerStatusChange.name: usdERXSysPowerStatusChange
usdERXSysPowerStatusChange.description: Reports a change in the status of a power element.

usdERXSysTempFanStatusChange.name: usdERXSysTempFanStatusChange
usdERXSysTempFanStatusChange.description: Reports a transition between the three states of the fan subsystem. When the fan subsystem transitions to the failed state the thermal protection hold off time begins.

usdERXSysTempStatusChange.name: usdERXSysTempStatusChange
usdERXSysTempStatusChange.description: Reports a change in the temperature status. When the status transitions to the tooHigh state the system enters thermal protection mode.

usdERXSysHighMemUtil.name: usdERXSysHighMemUtil
usdERXSysHighMemUtil.description: Report system memory utilization has met the conditions of usdERXSysHighMemUtilThreshold.

usdERXSysAbatedMemUtil.name: usdERXSysAbatedMemUtil
usdERXSysAbatedMemUtil.description: Reports system memory utilization has met the conditions of usdERXSysAbatedMemUtilThreshold.

usdERXSysTempProtectionStatusChange.name: usdERXSysTempProtectionStatusChange
usdERXSysTempProtectionStatusChange.description: Notification about changes in the state of Thermal Protection. This notification is sent when the tempProtectionStatus changes. It is also sent when the holdOffTimeRemaining is 50% of the holdOffTime.

usdERXSysCompliance.name: usdERXSysCompliance
usdERXSysCompliance.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities which implement the ERX System MIB. This compliance statement became obsolete when new slot information objects were added.

usdERXSysCompliance1.name: usdERXSysCompliance1
usdERXSysCompliance1.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities which implement the ERX System MIB. This compliance statement became obsolete when the timing group was added.

usdERXSysCompliance2.name: usdERXSysCompliance2
usdERXSysCompliance2.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities which implement the ERX System MIB. This compliance statement became obsolete when new memory information objects and notifications were added.

usdERXSysCompliance3.name: usdERXSysCompliance3
usdERXSysCompliance3.description: Obsolete compliance statement for entities which implement the ERX System MIB. This compliance statement became obsolete when new system temperature information objects and notifications were added.

usdERXSysCompliance4.name: usdERXSysCompliance4
usdERXSysCompliance4.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the ERX System MIB.

usdERXSysGroup.name: usdERXSysGroup
usdERXSysGroup.description: Obsolete collection of management objects pertaining to system capabilities in a Juniper product. This group became obsolete when new slot information objects were added.

usdERXSysNotifyGroup.name: usdERXSysNotifyGroup
usdERXSysNotifyGroup.description: Obsolete collection of management notifications pertaining to system operations in a Juniper product. This group became obsolete when new memory threshold notificaitons were added.

usdERXSysGeneralGroup.name: usdERXSysGeneralGroup
usdERXSysGeneralGroup.description: Obsolete collection of management objects pertaining to general system capabilities in a Juniper product. This group became obsolete when new memory management objects were added.

usdERXSysFabricGroup.name: usdERXSysFabricGroup
usdERXSysFabricGroup.description: A collection of management objects pertaining to system fabric capabilities in a Juniper product.

usdERXSysNvsGroup.name: usdERXSysNvsGroup
usdERXSysNvsGroup.description: A collection of management objects pertaining to non-volitile storage subsystem capabilities in a Juniper product.

usdERXSysSlotGroup.name: usdERXSysSlotGroup
usdERXSysSlotGroup.description: A collection of management objects pertaining to slot-specific system capabilities in a Juniper product.

usdERXSysPortGroup.name: usdERXSysPortGroup
usdERXSysPortGroup.description: A collection of management objects pertaining to port-related system capabilities in a Juniper product.
